% Generated by hand for mppi_evidence
\name{mppi_evidence}
\alias{mppi_evidence}
\title{Model evidence for an mPPI fit}
\description{
Summarises information-criteria support for the multivariate PPI model versus a task-only baseline, leveraging quantities stored by \code{mppi_fit()}.
}
\usage{
mppi_evidence(fit, aggregate = TRUE)
}
\arguments{
  \item{fit}{An object returned by \code{mppi_fit()} or a higher-level wrapper.}
  \item{aggregate}{Logical; when \code{TRUE} (default) the aggregate totals are returned alongside per-component statistics.}
}
\value{
When \code{aggregate = TRUE} a list with elements \code{per_column} (data frame with component-wise RSS, AIC/BIC, and deltas) and \code{aggregate} (one-row data frame of totals). When \code{aggregate = FALSE} only the per-component data frame is returned.
}
\details{
The statistics are computed from the residual sum-of-squares of the full design (confounds plus psychological regressors) and the baseline design (confounds only). Positive deltas indicate that the PPI-inclusive model improves the evidence relative to the baseline.
}
\author{multiPPI developers}
\seealso{\code{mppi_fit}, \code{mppi_hrf_ensemble}}
\examples{
set.seed(1)
Y <- matrix(rnorm(200), 100, 2)
X <- cbind(1, rnorm(100), rnorm(100))
fit <- mppi_fit(Y, X, psych_idx = 3)
ev <- mppi_evidence(fit)
head(ev$per_column)
}
